headline: What Woodward’s Changing Story Means For Valuation And Execution Through 2026
summary: Woodward’s latest update has shifted its fair value estimate from US$317.13 to US$413.00, with only modest tweaks to assumptions such as the discount rate and revenue growth. This reset is being shaped by recent Street research that reacts to Q4 results, management’s FY26 outlook, and the balance between sector support and execution risk in Aerospace & Defense. Stay tuned to see how you can keep on top of these changing assumptions and the evolving narrative around Woodward in the months...
